examples.en: I consign this evil book to the flames.
The goods were consigned to Australia.
The paintings were consigned to our care.
The shipment of apples was consigned to London.
The goods were consigned to him.
She consigned the painting to an auction house.
These goods are baled up and consigned to a factory abroad.
Traditionally young Masai men are consigned to a period of isolation in the bush in order to turn them into strong, lionhearted warriors.
